message.content: {"reasoning":"Both descriptions report that an NPC becomes frozen in a default T/A-pose, does not play normal walk/run/idle animations, and instead moves by sliding or gliding across the ground and up stairs while slightly floating. No conflicting details are present.","match":true}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug: helicopter rotor blades are motionless even though helicopter is flying. The visual error concerns the helicopter’s rotor animation.\nGenerated report: focuses on an enemy NPC that is hanging/floating under a helicopter because the rappel rope and animation are missing. It does not mention rotor blades at all; the helicopter’s flight is assumed normal. The symptom, cause, and affected asset (rope/NPC animation vs rotor blades) are different, so they are not the same underlying bug.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth highlights two specific anomalous behaviors occurring together: (1) a character standing on the helicopter who oscillates up-and-down, and (2) the helicopter’s rotor blades are completely still even though the aircraft is flying.  The generated report only describes the first part (a character spawning/standing on the rotor hub) and explicitly implies that the blades are still spinning (“ignoring collision with the spinning blades”). It also lacks mention of the rapid vertical oscillation and instead states the avatar is perfectly stationary. Because the second crucial symptom (frozen rotor blades) and the oscillation behavior are absent—and the generated report even contradicts the rotor-stopped condition—the two descriptions point to different underlying bugs.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Both descriptions deal with an ordinary ground vehicle that ends up airborne instead of being on the ground – i.e., the vehicle’s physics/gravity is broken so it floats in the sky.  The generated report and the ground-truth note the same unexpected state (a car floating in mid-air).  Although the ground-truth adds that the car is rotating and slowly moving away, while the generated report says the car “hover[s] without any movement,” these are secondary details; the fundamental bug (vehicle stuck in the air, unaffected by gravity) is identical.","match":true}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug: when an arrow hits an animal (deer) the animal is launched high into the air – the problem lies with excessive force applied to the hit creature.\nGenerated bug report: arrows themselves get stuck in the air when shot upward and never fall – the animal is not mentioned or affected. The symptom, object involved, and physics issue described are completely different.\nTherefore, they are not the same bug.","match":false}

Therefore they both describe the same underlying physics/collision issue when jumping onto a ship.","match":true}
